CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1945, pg. 21, reads: "What's the Joke? - Louis Armstrong and Anne [Ann] Baker are really killing themselves over something. Louis' band played here Monday night.  Anne was formerly featured vocalist with Louis, so she and Satchmo' got together for a gum session. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Louis "Satchmo" Armstrong, Ann Baker, and Pittsburgh Courier reporter George Brown, in booth at Crawford Grill No. 1
